ore a Buddhist, but I understand the Old Testament from the New. Be kind to the &quot;true Christians&quot;, after all they have been through, perhaps they deserve a little sympathy. Even more so now, because their religion is being hyjacked by Right Wing Zealots, just as the Muslim's religion is being hyjacked by violent fanatics as well. What a crazy world. &#10;I would venture that if a female student wore the traditional woman's Muslin garb to school, and carried the Koran in plain and open view, and if she was hauled down to the Principal's office, the lawsuits would fly and political correctness would be a dizzying array of rhetoric, so that no one would dare challenge the woman ever again in the school. The Principal would get censured and the the BOE would be warned and intimidated to &quot;get their mind's right.&quot; The hypocritical aspects of American society are incredible these days. &#10;Sad, indeed. This is one of the reasons why the government needs to get out of the business of education. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1298" language="en" documentId="1928" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="brien" date="12th September 2006 02:47 PM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=11753&amp;page=3" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1928" notes="" title="The Bible in Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="195"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="196" end="655"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="656" end="1191"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="1192" end="1298"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>